Real Madrid on Sunday celebrated winning the Champions League at Cibeles Square in the Spanish capital where they were greeted by partying fans. Real Madrid became European champions for a record extending 14th time after beating Liverpool 1-0 in a Champions League final at the Stade de France on Saturday. Carlo Ancelotti wrote his name in the history books by becoming the first coach to win the Champions League four times. Real Madrid goalkeeper Thibaut Courtois was the hero of the night on Saturday as his sensational performance between the posts ended Liverpool's Champions League dream in Paris. In his press conference following the final, former Chelsea keeper Courtois slammed his critics, saying he felt he did not get enough respect, particularly in England. (With input from AP)